The paper deals with detecting confusion from eye-tracking data, which is a domain related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for this task suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of engineered features, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
